WHAT KIND DATA IS SEND TO THE HUBSPOT CRM : 

Now you're asking:

What kind of data from all this can (and should) be sent to HubSpot, and why?

Letâ€™s go module by module, and Iâ€™ll tell you:

âœ… What kind of data you can send

ğŸš« What not to send

ğŸ§  Why to send it (what HubSpot does with it)

âœ… 1. User Registration & Login
Send to HubSpot:
email

first name, last name

phone number

signup date

user type (if admin/customer/vendor)

lead_source (e.g., "Website Signup", "Google Ads")

Why?
To create a Contact in HubSpot CRM

To enroll in a welcome automation (email, onboarding)

To track user lifecycle (lead â†’ customer)

âœ… 2. Admin Adding Products
Donâ€™t send to HubSpot directly ğŸš«
Why?

HubSpot is a CRM, not an e-commerce backend.

Product catalog is better managed in your DB or platforms like Shopify/WooCommerce.

But you can sync:

ğŸ”¹ Product metadata only if youâ€™re creating marketing automation based on product types.

âœ… 3. User Searching Products
This is optional but powerful.

You can log:
search keywords

searched categories

number of searches

search timestamp

Send as:
Custom Timeline Events

Or enrich the Contact record in HubSpot

Why?
To track user interests

Trigger marketing automation: â€œUser searched for â€˜shoesâ€™ â†’ send shoe promotionsâ€

âœ… 4. User Booking a Product (Order Placed)
Send to HubSpot:
product name

order amount

booking date

delivery address (partial)

order status (pending/confirmed)

payment method (UPI/COD)

Where?
As a Deal or Custom Object

Or as a timeline event on Contact

Why?
Track sales pipeline per user

Trigger follow-up emails: order confirmation, delivery updates

Allow sales/support team to manage orders

âœ… 5. User Paying the Amount
Send:
transaction ID

payment status (Success/Failed)

amount paid

payment date

Optional: Use for building a Deal pipeline in HubSpot.

Why?
Helps sales team see who paid

Segment contacts: Paid vs Not Paid

Trigger automated invoice, feedback survey, or thank-you mail

âœ… Summary Table

Module	Send to HubSpot?	What to Send	Why
User Signup/Login	âœ… Yes	Name, Email, Signup source	Create contact, trigger welcome
Admin Adds Product	ğŸš« No	(Optional metadata)	HubSpot not for inventory
User Search	âš ï¸ Optional	Search keywords, category	Behavior tracking & targeting
Booking Product	âœ… Yes	Order info, booking time	Track deals, sales pipeline
Payment	âœ… Yes	Amount, Status, Txn ID	Trigger thank-you flows, mark as customer
ğŸš« What NOT to Send

Field	Reason
Passwords	Security issue â€” never send
Full Address (optional)	Unless needed for CRM/sales use
Payment gateway tokens	Risky, better handled in your backend only
âœ… What HubSpot Will Do With This Data:
Create/update Contacts

Create Deals (representing orders)

Trigger Workflows (email follow-ups, reminders, automations)

Show in Dashboards for your sales/support teams

Allow you to segment users (by behavior, order status, payment history)

ğŸš€ Bonus: HubSpot CRM Automation Examples for You

